# PDF Splitting Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Split a source PDF into two separate PDF files:
1. `text_only.pdf`: Contains all extracted text, preserving layout as much as possible, with no images.
2. `images_only.pdf`: Contains all extracted images, preserving layout, with no text.

## Proposed Changes

### [Script]
#### [NEW] [split_pdf.py](file:///Users/vidyadhar/.gemini/antigravity/brain/c29a6940-ccd7-46dc-a7fb-df5f0fa55bc4/split_pdf.py)
- A Python script using `pymupdf` (fitz).
- Function `split_pdf(input_path, output_dir)`:
  - Opens `input_path`.
  - **Text-Only Generation**:
    - Creates a copy of the input PDF (or iterates pages).
    - Removes all image objects from each page (using `page.get_images()` and `page.delete_image()` or by redacting/cleaning drawings).
    - Saves as `text_only.pdf`.
  - **Image-Only Generation**:
    - Creates a copy of the input PDF.
    - Removes all text objects (using `page.get_text("dict")` or `page.add_redact_annot()` covering text bboxes and applying redactions).
    - Saves as `images_only.pdf`.

